<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-13298] DataOutputBuffer.asNewBuffer broken</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-13298</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The implementation of &lt;tt&gt;DataOutputBuffer.asNewBuffer()&lt;/tt&gt; reuses the underlying &lt;tt&gt;ByteBuffer&lt;/tt&gt; array. This is probably not an issue, but it is definitely incorrect and may lead to incorrect/overwritten information returned by &lt;tt&gt;SystemKeyspace.truncationAsMapEntry&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
